Parliament, Wednesday, 28 August 2019 – The Select Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs will tomorrow, 29 August 2019, visit JB Marks and Madibeng Local Municipality in the North West Province to do an In-Loco oversight visit as mandated by the constitution. Due to time constraints, the committee will now only be visiting JB Marks Local Municipality tomorrow. The visit follows a decision taken by the North West Provincial Executive to intervene in the municipality as per Section 139 (1)(b) of the Constitution. This decision followed various challenges within the municipalities.  The committee will visit the municipality to assess if it must recommend to the National Council of Provinces to accede to the intervention by the Provincial Executive. The National Council of Provinces is mandated by Section 139 (2)(c) to, review the intervention regularly and may make any appropriate recommendation to the provincial executive while the intervention continues. This oversight visit is in keeping with this Constitutional directive. The committee will use the visit to interact with stakeholders including the MEC responsible for Cooperative Governance, Councillors and Ward Committee Members, organised labour and other representative forums. Details of the Visit Date: 29 August 2019
	Venue: JB Marks Local Municipal offices
	Time: 9:00 Details of Madibeng Visit Date: 29 August 2019
	Venue: Madibeng Local Municipal offices, Brits
	Time: 14:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON COOPERATIVE GOVERNANCE AND TRADITIONAL AFFAIRS, MR CHINA DODOVU 
	
